Problem Statement-2
                    Alert Triage Workflow
1. Problem Statement
Security teams receive many alerts from different cloud providers such as AWS, Azure, and GCP. Many of these alerts are noisy, lack context, and require engineers to jump between multiple tools to investigate them. As a result, security engineers spend a lot of time trying to understand whether an alert is actually important and what action they need to take.
This design aims to create a simple and clear alert triage workflow that helps security engineers quickly understand an alert, investigate its details, and fix the issue from one place.

2. User Persona: Security Engineer
Role: Mid-level Cloud Security Engineer
 Goals:
●Understand if an alert is real or false

●Quickly check the impacted resource

●Take the right action with confidence

Pain Points:
●Too many alerts, leading to “alert fatigue”

●Lack of context around why the alert happened

●Switching between tools to gather logs, cloud details, and permissions

●Uncertainty about the impact of making a fix


Motivations:
●Reduce investigation time

●Improve accuracy of triage decisions

●Maintain a secure cloud environment

